{
  "texts": [
    "Hence, we can consider f ad as a section of (adM 1) * ⊗ (adM 2).",
    "By (12), f ad is parallel with respect to the induced flat connection: hence, we can identify f ad with an element of Aut(𝔫) such thatf ad • ρ 1, * (γ) = ρ 2, * (γ) • f ad.",
    "Since N is simply connected, we can integrate f ad to f ∈ Aut(N) which satisfies f • ρ 1 (γ) = ρ 2 (γ) • f. Then, recalling the identification Mi ≃ B × N given by the flat connections, the map B × N → B × N, (b, x) → (b, f (x)), descends to a map f: M 1 → M 2.",
    "The map f is isometric since f * (H 1) = H 2 and f * (V 1) = V 2, it covers an isometry, and f * ad h 2 = h 1.",
    "□ 2.4.Ricci curvature of invariant metrics."
  ]
}